<p>This is the help page for the Online Knowledge Management System (OKMS).</p>
<p>OKMS is a web-based application that helps organizations manage their knowledge. It allows users to create, store, and share knowledge in a variety of formats, including documents, images, videos, and links.</p>
<p>OKMS is also a collaboration tool. It allows users to work together on knowledge posts, add comments, and vote on posts.</p>
<h2>Getting Started</h2>
<p>To get started with OKMS, you will need to create an account. Once you have created an account, you can log in and start creating knowledge posts.</p>
<p>To create a knowledge post, click on the "Ask question" box. You will then be able to enter the title, content, and other elements for your post.</p>
<p>Once you have finished creating your post, click on the "Post" button to make it available to other users.</p>
<h2>Using OKMS</h2>
<p>Once you have created some knowledge posts, you can start using OKMS to manage your knowledge.</p>
<p>To find a knowledge post, you can use the search bar at the right sidebar of the page. You can also browse through the different courses.</p>
<p>To view a knowledge post, click on the title of the post. You will then be able to read the post, add comments, and vote on the post.</p>
<h2>Collaborating with Other Users</h2>
<p>OKMS is a collaboration tool, which means that you can work together with other users on knowledge posts.</p>
<p>To collaborate on an post, you can add comments to the post. You can also vote on posts.</p>
<p>When you add a comment to an post, the author of the post will be notified.</p>
<p>When you vote on an post, your vote will be counted towards the post's rating. Posts with higher ratings will be more visible to other users.</p>
